               whole mouse cortex",
  author    = "Tournissac, Marine and Boido, Davide and Omn{\`e}s, Manon and
               Houssen, Yannick Goulam and Ciobanu, Luisa and Charpak, Serge",
  abstract  = "Significance: All functional brain imaging methods have
               technical drawbacks and specific spatial and temporal resolution
               limitations. Unraveling brain function requires bridging the
               data acquired with cellular and mesoscopic functional imaging.
               This imposes the access to animal preparations, allowing
               longitudinal and multiscale investigations of brain function in
               anesthetized and awake animals. Such preparations are optimal to
               study normal and pathological brain functions while reducing the
               number of animals used. Aim: To fulfill these needs, we
